1. route(/api/posts/1)
2. Body
{
    postId:2;
    title:"This is my tweet"
}
3. Headers-Metadata
4. query parameters(/api/posts?postId=1)

# Middlewares
-> in express.js,middlewares refers to functions that have access to the request objects ,response object and the next function in the application req-res cycle.
->modifying req or res objects
->Ending req-res cycle
->calling the next middleware function in the stack


# cors-cross origin resource sharing
by default cors are blocked,to use it then we have to use cors middleware
